   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Improving Literacy in Puerto Rico 2020- 2021</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">MRC&apos;s certified Orton-Gillingham interventionists provide critical literacy skills through daily small group reading interventions to 70 students from marginalized communities in San Juan. These kindergarten through 3rd graders struggle in the process of learning to read due to untreated factors including dyslexia and learning disabilities, placing them at risk for academic failure. Invest in the future of Puerto Rico by increasing their chance for success during the 2020-21 school year.</narrative>
  </description>
